    "description": "This is a game made by a <strong>14-year old. </strong><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Welcome to Five Nights At Pt's II!</h2><br>Instead of a pizzeria, Anthony and his friends have moved to a different place: your bedroom. <br><br>Why are they there? Play until the end to find out. <br><br><br>Play through five nights of intense gameplay, closing doors and managing your power level. and oxygen. <br>After each night, complete the post-shift by fending off three enemies while trying to finish tasks. <br>After that, play an 8-bit inspired cutscene that progresses you through the story. <br><br><strong>This game was developed using Scratch</strong> and complied using Turbowarp and Electron. This means that cloud saves will not work, although the developers at APTStudios have accounted for this by implementing a save and load code system similar to NES games. We apologize for the inconvenience.<br><br>Don't let the fact that it was developed using Scratch fool you. This is a full game in and out, ruthlessly playtested by more than 40 people over a course of 2 months.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Featuring:</h2><br>5200 lines of code<br><br>49 sprites<br><br>408 scripts<br><br>Over 600 frames of animation<br><br>Fully playable retro cutscenes!",
